# NestJS Backend Rules

## Architecture
- Match existing module structure: AuthModule, TradeModule, DatabaseModule
- New routes go in existing controllers unless a genuinely new module is needed
- New DB queries follow existing TypeORM repository pattern in services
- Never add new entities without updating backendReadme.md Section 5

## Database Rules
- synchronize: true is enabled — new nullable columns auto-migrate on restart
- Never write migration files manually
- All new columns must be nullable or have defaults to avoid breaking existing rows

## Route Rules
- Every new route must be added to SYSTEM_CONTRACT_MATRIX.md Section 3.1 or 3.2
- Match existing error handling: NotFoundException, UnauthorizedException
- No JWT guards — verify-node pattern is the auth mechanism

## WebSocket Rules
- Never rename or add new global socket events without updating Section 4 of matrix
- Room naming convention is room_master_<userId> — never change this pattern